# ================================================================= #
#          ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES FOR EDBOT WHATSAPP BOT           #
# ================================================================= #

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# SESSION_ID (Recommended for Production / Deployments)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# This variable holds your WhatsApp session data. Using it allows your
# bot to restart without needing to scan the QR code every time.
#
# HOW TO GET IT:
# 1. Leave this variable EMPTY on your first run.
# 2. Run the bot: `npm start` or `node index.js`.
# 3. Scan the QR code that appears in your terminal.
# 4. After a successful login, a new SESSION_ID will be printed in the console.
# 5. Copy the ENTIRE string (it's very long) and paste it here.
#
# WHERE TO USE IT:
# - Docker: Pass it as an environment variable (`-e SESSION_ID="..."`).
# - Railway/Render/Heroku: Add it to the "Environment Variables" or "Secrets" section in your service settings.
# - Local Development: You can paste it here to test the environment variable mode.
#
SESSION_ID=""


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# OTHER CONFIGURATIONS (Optional)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# You can add other environment variables here to configure your bot,
# for example, an API key for a service it uses.
#
# EXAMPLE_API_KEY="your_api_key_here"
